  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Is it safe to repair a broken spring myself?</span><span class="faq-arrow">&#9654;</span></div><div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Torsion and extension springs are under high tension and can cause serious injury. Leave spring repairs to trained professionals.</p></div></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Why won’t my garage door open even though the opener runs?</span><span class="faq-arrow">&#9654;</span></div><div class="faq-answer"><p>This could mean a broken spring, disconnected trolley, or stripped gear. We’ll diagnose and fix the root issue safely.</p></div></div>
